                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/21138: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName type="from"
                            >Harrison</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-22T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 22, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 22—2:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1655. My telegram no. 1436, April 10.<note n="25" xml:id="d828fn25">Not printed;
                        it reported that the American communication to the Hungarian Government had
                        been delivered by the Swiss Legation in Budapest at 11 a.m. on April 7; the
                        Hungarian authorities had made no comment (740.0011 European War
                        1939/20921).</note> Swiss Foreign Office has today advised me that the Swiss
                    Minister in Budapest has reported by telegraph the receipt of a <hi
                        rend="italic">note verbale</hi> dated April 17 from Hungarian Foreign Office
                    stating that in taking note of our communication Foreign Office recalls the
                    attack by Soviet Air Forces on Kassa<note n="26" xml:id="d828fn26">City in that
                        portion of Slovakia annexed by Hungary from Czechoslovakia as a result of
                        the arbitral award by the Italian-German Commission made at Vienna, November
                        2, 1938, In Slovak, the name was Košice.</note> June 26 last causing
                    enormous losses in lives and property. Accordingly Hungary considers that she is
                    carrying on a defensive war against the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
